channel.title: Cant find these colours in my css, Help xd
channel.description:
So i was messing with the css of my new hiscores, im trying to put it into the same style as my website, and my forums.
[img]http://i32.servimg.com/u/f32/16/52/06/54/for_mo10.jpg[/img]
but there are a few brown spots left, wich i cant find in the css, when i eyedrop it in photoshop, I should get a #4c350a Like this for example. So i printscreened it, and putted it in photoshop to use the eyedropper tool on it, it gives the # but i can't find those numbers in my css. I also looked for pictures and even in the php files, but no results
Could someone please help me with this ;)

item.title: Cant find these colours in my css, Help xd
item.dc:creator: @The_Web_Guy The Web Guy
item.description:
@The_Web_Guy wrote:

If you’re using google chrome right-click the area and click ‘inspect element’ then look to the right side and it’ll tell you.

EDIT:

The search box and ‘go to divine forums’ are actually images.
Search Box: /imgs/hiscores/search_small.png
Last divine Forums Box: /imgs/hiscores/search_large.png

The Scroll Bar is in hiscores-28.css (line 680) [#3B2B0F]

.arrow_back { background-color: #3B2B0F; }

As for the Prayer look for this: [#3B2B0F]

element.style { background-color: #4C350A; }

Goodluck.
